        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 9:16PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 916 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fordtran, or 12 miles southeast of Yoakum, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Speaks, Ezzell, and Hope.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
